  "title": "Cyber Support Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities</strong></p><p>EDR Operations & Maintenance</p><ul><li>Maintain and operate Carbon Black (CB) EDR servers hosted on RHEL8.</li><li>Perform scheduled maintenance tasks on Operating System (OS),\ndatabases and application (CB) level, including patching, health checks, backups, and service restarts.</li><li>Validate and maintain EDR server application services (web console, CB backend services, Solr, PostgreSQL) and log forwarding services (NXLog, CB event forwarder) to the Log Collector.</li><li>Monitor and clear stale services, queues, or indexing issues.</li><li>Manual review of system, security and audit logs of OS, database\nand application which are not forwarded to the designated log collection server</li><li>Engage support from OEM to provide troubleshooting solution,\nprofessional services for hardware and software related configuration, integration and troubleshooting works, if necessary.</li><li>Manage endpoint sensors and monitor the presence, health, and\nconnectivity of all sensors</li><li>Troubleshoot “offline” sensors.</li><li>Assist in onboarding new hosts into the EDR environment.</li><li>Validate asset inventory.</li><li>Network & Infrastructure Coordination</li><li>Responsible to ensure the security & hardening for EDR server\nis in accordance to guidelines.</li><li>Participate in quarterly and annual reviews. Responsible to put reviews for approvals.</li><li>Provide technical support for issues</li><li>Reporting & documentation</li></ul><p><strong>Mandatory Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Experience with Carbon Black EDR, or equivalent EDR platforms.</li><li>Strong RHEL system administration knowledge (RHEL 8/9).</li><li>Familiarity with PostgreSQL maintenance tasks (backup, check,\nrestore).</li><li>Understanding of network troubleshooting (TCP, TLS, proxies,\nfirewalls).</li><li>Hands-on experience with endpoint diagnostics for EDR sensors on\nWindows.</li><li>Understanding of secure operations and handling of privileged\naccounts.</li></ul>",
